How long is the incubation period of new coronary pneumonia? Recent cases have challenged previous estimates that the maximum incubation period for new pneumonia is 14 days.

On the morning of February 17,2020, Heyuan City, Guangdong Province, announced a confirmed case. The patient took a train back to Heyuan from Wuhan. He was released from medical observation for 14 days on February 8. After 6 days, he began to cough without apparent cause and was finally diagnosed.

In addition, Liu in Rizhao, Shandong Province, was quarantined on January 20 with a family of four because of exposure to a confirmed case. There was no abnormality during the isolation period. However, 10 days after the end of the isolation period, Liu began to develop symptoms such as cough and fever, on February 15, she was diagnosed with new crown pneumonia.

The news came after Yibin, Sichuan Province, reported the diagnosis of a new case of pneumonia on Feb. 11. The case lasted 16 days from January 23, when he returned from Wuhan, to the onset of mild cough, and the onset of fever occurred on day 18. The city of Guilin, Guangxi Province, also reported a confirmed case of Yangxingxin pneumonia on Feb. 6, with an incubation period of more than 14 days.

Regarding the incubation period of the new coronavirus, the previously published official pneumonia diagnosis and treatment plan for COVID-19 infection (trial version 5) shows that based on the current epidemiological investigation, the incubation period is 1-14 days, usually 3-7 days. This is the standard for people everywhere to be quarantined for 14 days to check for infection.

Ma Xiaowei, director of the State Health and Construction Commission, also said at a news conference held in the State Council Information Office on January 26 that from the observation, the incubation period of the COVID-19 is about 10 days, with the longest incubation period being 14 days, and it is still infectious in the incubation period, which is very different from SARS.

According to the data released by the World Health Organization, the incubation period of SARS virus is from 2 to 10 days. The incubation period of SARS virus varies among individuals depending on the route of transmission, the amount of virus infected and other factors such as immunity. As can be seen, the incubation period of COVID-19 is longer than that of SARS.

In an interview with Interface News, Tong Yi, Dean of the Beijing University of Chemical Technology and a member of the Chinese Medical Association's Microbiology and Immunology Committee, stressed that, "incubation period" actually refers to the time from the patient infected with the virus to the first symptoms, not many people think of the time from the individual infected to the final diagnosis.

"Due to a variety of factors, some cases may take longer to be diagnosed, but the incubation period does not exceed 14 days. ". Tong said the incubation period of COVID-19 had not lengthened and the virus could not have mutated so quickly after the outbreak. Some extreme cases may be due to the fact that some cases observed as a result of the increasing number of cases are normal.

Tong yi-gang believes that although the timing of the onset of symptoms is also influenced by a variety of factors, such as individual genotypes and their own physiological conditions, most people will have symptoms within 2 to 14 days, only in rare cases does the incubation period increase.

Notably, a paper by Chinese Academy of Engineering Academician Zhong Nanshan's team on 10 February reviewed the clinical characteristics of 1,099 patients (as of 29 January) with newly diagnosed pneumonia. The results showed that the median incubation period of NCP was 3 days and up to 24 days.

Zhong Nanshan told the media that the results of the study showed a greater polarization of the incubation period of COVID-19, with varying lengths of incubation.

Yang Gonghuan, an expert in public health and Epidemiology and former deputy director of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, said in response to recent cases of extremely long incubation periods found in various places, at present, the outside world's understanding of the COVID-19 is still not in-depth, we are required to follow the process of epidemic prevention and control, the occurrence of extreme cases of in-depth discussion and analysis, more detailed study. She pointed out that it was important not to jump to conclusions without knowing the exact situation and that the population should not be alarmed by the appearance of specific cases.

Yang stressed that while it was not possible to confirm the existence of the very long incubation period of the new coronavirus, it was certain that the proportion of such cases was not high.

Zhong Nanshan has previously stressed that although studies show the longest incubation period is 24 days, there is only one case of the disease out of 1,099, and it is not scientific to use this single case as the longest incubation period of the disease.

Even so, some places in the prevention and control of the epidemic in order to be on the safe side, began to extend the isolation time of 14 days spontaneously. Yang Gonghuan said, the local self-establishment of the quarantine period is not scientific, or should be the National Health Commission recommended the quarantine period prevail. "If there are a lot of infected people in a place, it's not impossible to extend the quarantine a little bit, but if it's extended indefinitely, it's bound to be controversial, " she said
